Amphiprora aboensis n. sp. — Pl. 1, f. 1.

Frustule silioious, slightly constricted, 42 μ in length;

half of its breadth 12 μ.. Valve with a rather low keel; junction-line straight.

Striation of the keel and valve equal; striae 9 in 10 μ, strong,

indistinotly punctate.

Foss.: Ab. Hindersmossen13 rare.

As I have seen only a half frustule, the diagnosis must be incomplete. Still, this speeies seems well distinguished, especially by the strong striation, from other forms of the

genus Amphiprora.
